column5: Heading to minnitaki fri very hyped up. Does any one have a fishing report to share. Looking for depth color anything i can chew on thanks
Just got back. Walleye at 22 feet, water 72 degrees white jigs and crawlers. Slow but still great fishing.
Fished Minnitaki on Friday. Similarly hitting eyes at 18-22 feet. Jig and minnows worked fine for me. Water is down, but about average for this time of year in my opinion. Good luck and enjoy!
